-- Australian and N.Z. Stocks: Caltex, Newcrest Mining, St. Barbara, Wattyl
-- Shani Raja
-- 2010-06-28T04:30:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/australian-and-n-z-stocks-csr-newcrest-santos-st-barbara-woodside.html

          
          
             Australia’s  S&P/ASX 200 Index 
dropped 0.7 percent to 4,381.20 as of 2:29 p.m. in Sydney. New
Zealand’s  NZX 50 Index  lost 0.7 percent to 3,012.41 in
Wellington.  
 The following were among the most active shares in the
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names.  
 Gold producers: Gold rose for a second day in New York on
June 25, gaining 0.8 percent to $1,256.20 an ounce on the Comex.  
 Newcrest Mining Ltd.  (NCM AU), Australia’s biggest gold
producer, gained 0.2 percent to A$36.08. St. Barbara Ltd. (SBM
AU) climbed 2.8 percent to 37 Australian cents.  
  Caltex Australia Ltd.  (CTX AU) slumped 2.6 percent to
A$9.41. The stock was downgraded to “hold” from “buy” at
Deutsche Bank AG by equity analyst John Hirjee.  
      Wattyl Ltd.  (WYL AU) jumped 28 percent to A$1.61. The
Australian paintmaker agreed to a A$142 million ($124 million)
takeover offer from coating-manufacturer Valspar Corp.  
